{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Choose a rectangular loaf tin (metal, 20 cm long) that fits in the Varoma dish, grease with butter and dust with semolina, then set aside.","Place spelt grains in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>1 min\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place 250 g water, treacle (if using) and yeast in mixing bowl and warm <nobr>2 min\/37Â°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add reserved ground spelt, bread flour, balsamic vinegar, salt and sunflower seeds and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to prepared loaf tin, dust surface with flour and cover with heat-resistant cling film. Place loaf tin in Varoma dish and allow dough to rise for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl.","Place 1000 g water in mixing bowl, set Varoma in position and steam <nobr>50 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr> (for silicone baking moulds see tip).","Remove Varoma, take out loaf tin and remove cling film then leave to cool in tin for 10 minutes. Transfer bread from tin to a wire rack and allow to cool before slicing and serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 Tbsp butter, for greasing","2 Tbsp semolina, for dusting","250 g spelt grains","1250 g water","10 g dark treacle              (optional)","20 g fresh yeast, crumbled","50 g bread flour, plus extra for dusting","10 g balsamic vinegar","1 tsp salt","100 g sunflower seeds"]}],"id":"r150929","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-p6sO1lfAIwk\/XZavJ4N0s5I\/AAAAAAAAhsQ\/t8ZHGropbaAhiVBVC5d9cqwJWUzGK8kKwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_t94tW0OjHQPjSPe2.png","title":"Steamed Wholemeal Bread","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"4 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"12 g","calories":"409 kJ \/ 98 kcal"},"usefulItems":"loaf tin (metal, 20 cm long), heat-resistant cling film, wire rack","hintsAndTricks":["<i>This bread is made without an oven! The result is moist and full of flavour, and the whole grains add extra nutrition. If you are not in a hurry, reduce the yeast and give the bread more time to rise, as described in the variation.<\/i>","If using a silicone bread mould, extend steaming time by <nobr>10 minutes.<\/nobr>","For a longer rise, the amount of fresh yeast can be halved in <nobr>step 4<\/nobr> allow covered bread dough to rise for <nobr>2-3 hours<\/nobr> in a warm place or overnight in the fridge, then continue with <nobr>step 5.<\/nobr><br>- <strong>Nut Bread:<\/strong> Instead of sunflower seeds, add <nobr>80 g nuts<\/nobr> (hazelnuts or walnuts).<br>- <strong>Carrot Bread:<\/strong> After <nobr>step 2,<\/nobr> place <nobr>100 g carrots,<\/nobr> cut in pieces, in mixing bowl and chop <nobr><strong>4 sec\/speed 5.<\/strong><\/nobr> Leave carrots in mixing bowl and continue with recipe.<br>- <strong>Carrot Walnut Bread:<\/strong> After <nobr>step 2,<\/nobr> place <nobr>80 g carrots,<\/nobr> cut in pieces, in mixing bowl and chop <nobr><strong>4 sec\/speed 5.<\/strong><\/nobr> Leave carrots in mixing bowl and continue with recipe. In <nobr>step 4<\/nobr> replace the <nobr>100 g sunflower<\/nobr> seeds with <nobr>30 g walnuts<\/nobr>."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h","20 slices"]}